üîπ Hashing kya hota hai?
Hashing ek process hai jisme plain text data ko ek fixed-length ke unreadable value (hash) me convert kiya jata hai.
Important point: 
            - Hashing one-way process hota hai. 
            - Hash se original data wapas nahi nikala ja sakta.

üîπ Hashing ki need kyun hoti hai?
Socho tumne database me aise data rakha:
                                      Username: meraz
                                      Password: 123456
  ‚ùå Problem:
           - Agar hacker DB hack kar le ‚Üí password directly mil jayega
           - Sab users risk me aa jayenge.



üîπ Plain Text ‚ùå ‚Üí Encryption ‚ùå ‚Üí Hashing ‚úÖ (Flow) :

1Ô∏è‚É£ Plain Text Storage (‚ùå Worst) :
                                 - password = "123456"
                                          - Easy to read.
                                          - Hacker ko direct mil jata hai.
2Ô∏è‚É£ Encryption (‚ö†Ô∏è Better but not best) :
                                  - Encrypted password = "A@x9#Lp"
                                                   - Data hide hota hai.
                                                   - Lekin decryption key hoti hai.
                                                   - Agar key leak ho gayi ‚Üí password wapas mil jayega.
3Ô∏è‚É£ Hashing (‚úÖ Best for passwords) :
                                - password = "123456"
                                  hash = "$2a$10$hjs7Kjs9..."
                                         - Hash se original password kabhi wapas nahi milta.
                                         - Even developer bhi nahi dekh sakta password.
                                         - Hacker ke liye useless.

üîπ Real Life Example :
üèß ATM PIN Example : ATM machine kya karta hai?
1Ô∏è‚É£ Tum PIN enter karte ho :
                           - PIN = 1234
2Ô∏è‚É£ ATM uska hash banata hai:
                       - hash(1234) = X9@kLp
3Ô∏è‚É£ Database me already stored hota hai:
                           - X9@kLp
4Ô∏è‚É£ Compare hota hai:
                  - Entered PIN ka hash == Stored hash ?
‚úîÔ∏è Match ‚Üí Access
‚ùå No match ‚Üí Reject.



Note:- Java me hash table ek concept hai, koi separate class nahi. HashMap aur Hashtable dono is concept ke alag implementations hain, aur dono Map interface ko implement karte hain.

üì¶ hash table (Concept) :
--------------------------
üîπ Definition :
Hash table ek data structure concept hai jo hashing technique ka use karke data ko key‚Äìvalue pairs ke form me store karta hai aur fast insertion, search aur deletion provide karta hai.

üîπ Key Idea :
Key se hash ‚Üí hash se index ‚Üí index par key‚Äìvalue store.




üîπ Hash Function Design Techniques (for Hash Tables) :
------------------------------------------------------

1Ô∏è‚É£ Division Method :
üîπ Formula : h(k) = k % m                                                            search keys ->   {11,10,66,58,74}      
                          k ‚Üí key                                                                           .............
                          m ‚Üí table size                                                                  0 |  11       |
                                                                                                            |           |
                                                                                                            '''''''''''''
                                                                                                          1 |           |
2Ô∏è‚É£ Mid-Square Method :                                                                                      |           |   
üîπ Steps :                                                                                                   ''''''''''''
      - Key ka square karo.                                                                                2 |           |
      - Beech ke digits uthao.                                                                               |           |
      - üîπ Example : (2-digit index chahiye)                                                                 '''''''''''''
                             Key = 11                                                                      3 |   58      |
                             Square = 121                                                                    |           |
                             Pad with 0 ‚Üí 0121                                                               '''''''''''''
                             Middle 2 digits ‚Üí 12                                                          4 |           |
               Zero padding allowed hai ‚úîÔ∏è                                                                   |           |
                                                                                                              ''''''''''''
                                                                                                           5 |           |
3Ô∏è‚É£ Digit Folding Method :                                                                                    |           |
üîπ Idea :                                                                                                     ''''''''''''
      - Key ke digits ko parts me tod ke add karo.                                                         6 |           |
      - üîπ Example :                                                                                         |           |
                    Key = 123456                                                                             '''''''''''''
                    Fold ‚Üí 12 + 34 + 56 = 102                                                              7 |           |
                    Index = 102 % tableSize                                                                  |           |
üîπ Use :                                                                                                     '''''''''''''
      - Jab key bahut badi ho (mobile number).                                                             8 |   74      |
                                                                                                             |           |
                                                                                                             '''''''''''''
                                                                                                           9 |           |
                                                                                                             |           |
                                                                                                             '''''''''''''
                                                                                                          10 |  10       |
                                                                                                             |           |
                                                                                                             '''''''''''''
                                                                                                                HASHTABLE  with size m = 11

For finding Hash function interview friendly and most easy way :
1Ô∏è‚É£ Division Method :
                  suppose take key as 11 and h-table size= 11
so based on formula :
                 key % h-table size
              => 11 % 11 = 0
               so on 0 index keep 11 as key.



                                                                       Collision Resolution 


Collision kya hoti hai?
Jab do ya zyada different keys ka hash same index (bucket) par aa jaye.
hash(k1) % n = 5
hash(k2) % n = 5   ‚Üê collision

üõ†Ô∏è Collision Resolution Techniques :
1Ô∏è‚É£ Closed Hashing / Open Addressing ?
Collision hone par same table ke kisi aur empty slot me element rakhte hain.









